{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/pulls/23991", "id": 32562521, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MzI1NjI1MjE=", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/23991", "diff_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/23991.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/pull/23991.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/23991", "number": 23991, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Don't expand vector if there is nothing left to write into it.", "user": {"login": "ghost", "id": 10137, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwMTM3", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/10137?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost", "html_url": "https://github.com/ghost", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/ghost/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "body": "A common C++ pattern is as follows:\n\nvector v;\nv.reserve(size);\n// add size elements to v in some way, without v being required to expand\n\nIn Rust, users will equivalently do the following:\nlet mut v = Vec::with_capacity(size);\n// add size elements to v in some way, without v being required to expand\n\nThe method read_to_end violates this expectation, by increasing the amount of space the vector is taking if the buffer being currently read in is exactly the right size required.\n\nThis results in a large performance drop in these cases- I attach benchmarking code and results.  This PR fixes this, so that if read_to_end is called with exactly the correct number of bytes allocated, the vector will not expand in size.\n\n```\n#![feature(test)]\nextern crate test;\nuse std::io::Read;\n\n#[bench]\nfn read_to_end_1024(b: &mut test::Bencher) {\n    let buf = [1u8; 1024];\n    let mut src = &buf[..];\n    let mut dst = Vec::with_capacity(1024);\n    b.iter(|| {\n        test::black_box(src.read_to_end(&mut dst))\n    });\n}\n\n#[bench]\nfn read_to_end_64k(b: &mut test::Bencher) {\n    let buf = [1u8; 1024 * 64];\n    let mut src = &buf[..];\n    let mut dst = Vec::with_capacity(64);\n    b.iter(|| {\n        test::black_box(src.read_to_end(&mut dst))\n    });\n}\n\n#[bench]\nfn read_to_end_normal_test(b: &mut test::Bencher) {\n    let buf = [1u8; 100000];\n    let mut src = &buf[..];\n    let mut dst = Vec::new();\n    b.iter(|| {\n        test::black_box(src.read_to_end(&mut dst))\n    });\n}\n\n#[bench]\nfn read_to_end_small_test(b: &mut test::Bencher) {\n    let buf = [1u8; 1000];\n    let mut src = &buf[..];\n    let mut dst = Vec::new();\n    b.iter(|| {\n        test::black_box(src.read_to_end(&mut dst))\n    });\n}\n\n#[test]\nfn read_to_end_doesnt_expand_capacity_unless_necessary() {\n    const BUF_SIZE: usize = 1024;\n    let buf = [1u8; BUF_SIZE];\n    let mut src = &buf[..];\n    let mut dst = Vec::with_capacity(BUF_SIZE);\n    let init_capacity = dst.capacity();\n    assert_eq!(src.read_to_end(&mut dst).unwrap(), BUF_SIZE);\n    assert_eq!(init_capacity, dst.capacity());\n}\n\n/*\nResults on my machine:\n\nWithout Modification:\n\ntest read_to_end_1024        ... bench:      9972 ns/iter (+/- 2666)\ntest read_to_end_64k         ... bench:   2568395 ns/iter (+/- 793768)\ntest read_to_end_normal_test ... bench:   2133921 ns/iter (+/- 554167)\ntest read_to_end_small_test  ... bench:     10703 ns/iter (+/- 2967)\n\n\nWith Modification:\n\ntest read_to_end_1024            ... bench:       750 ns/iter (+/- 30)\ntest read_to_end_64k              ... bench:     74184 ns/iter (+/- 14296)\ntest read_to_end_normal_test  ... bench:   1525546 ns/iter (+/- 200031)\ntest read_to_end_small_test   ... bench:      5651 ns/iter (+/- 1128)\n*/\n```\n", "created_at": "2015-04-03T00:31:12Z", "updated_at": "2015-04-03T21:01:51Z", "closed_at": "2015-04-03T21:01:51Z", "merged_at": null, "merge_commit_sha": "292adc8e099fce0cad8dba999e51b4ff43d07ad6", "assignee": {"login": "alexcrichton", "id": 64996, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY0OTk2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/64996?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton", "html_url": "https://github.com/alexcrichton", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "assignees": [{"login": "alexcrichton", "id": 64996, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY0OTk2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/64996?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton", "html_url": "https://github.com/alexcrichton", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/alexcrichton/starred{/owner}{/r